Mar 17 2005	Excellent location has a certain 'charm'	I stayed at Beck's in 2004. The location can't be beat, in the heart of the gay district, with lots of bars, restaurants and shops. There is a lot within walking distance. Free parking on site is a great bonus. The staff is friendly. The rooms are adequate but clean. There is a lot of cruising on the premises, but the guys are not aggressive (unless you want them to be)! The rooms can be very warm, so if you leave your window or door open, it can be interpreted that you are looking for company.	
Feb 8 2005	If you're in the Castro this can't be beat	I have stayed at Beck's countless times. Aside from the fact that it's perfectly located within walking distance of Castro Street, all manner of public transportation, great shops and restaurants, and the many bars that the Castro is famous for, it's also a well kept up establishment. Its a MOTEL, people. A Motor Lodge, just as it's called. I, for one, do not spend hours in my room when I'm in SF. There's just too much to do! But it's a great homebase from which to journey out from. As far as the cruising issue goes, the clientele is predominantly gay men, so cruising is a given. And I find that if you don't engage them, no one will engage you. Just mind your business, and basically they'll mind theirs. If you're that sqeamish, maybe you should be thinking about taking your vacation in a different area, because you will be cruised just as much if not more so walking down Market Street!! San Francisco is one of the great walking (and climbing) cities in the world, and Beck's so located that you can head out almost in any direction and find all of the things you have come to the City to find and see. Ignore the naysayers.	
Jan 3 2005 	Great location for gay visitors	I've stayed at Beck's for over 15 years whenever I am in SF. This is a gay-friendly motel in the heart of the Castro. It's clean, well-located and there are plenty of good places to eat and shop within walking distance. Public transit is near so you can just park in their lot and never have to drive while in SF (or get a parking ticket).	
Dec 10 2004	A Castro Tradition!	Beck's is not a fancy hotel, nor does it try to be. It is a motor lodge in the gayest part of a gay city. Expect anything different and you will be disappointed.Pros - Free onsite parking, adjacent to public transportation access, relatively inexpensive, great location.Cons - Few amenities, can be loud, no-frillsAll and all, we love Beck's, and we stay there whenever we are visiting San Francisco.	
